## Context
Author directive (2026-07-10, 0152 letter session): "I want a Fable-led
manuscript revision to align the style on my voice, based on comparative
samples (few shot learning)." The v2.0.5 English base was style-anchored once
at translation time (ticket 0173), but the R&R children (0134-0143) and the
appendix build-out accreted prose from many sessions. The response letter is
now first-person singular; the manuscript still uses the authorial "we" —
the voice/person question is settled with the author at kickoff, not assumed.

## Relevant files
- `deliverables/manuscript/manuscript.qmd` — the text to align
- `docs/style-anchor-v205.md` — curated samples of the author's pre-AI English
  prose (6 sources + 1 French register anchor); the few-shot base
- `config/ai-tells.yml` + `tests/test_manuscript_prose.py` — mechanical guards
- `.claude/rules/writing.md` (ghost mode), `docs/editorial-brief.md` — standing
  editorial decisions

## Actions
1. Kickoff with the author: settle voice decisions (we→I?, British-English
   consistency, hedging register, question-closings).
2. Build the few-shot set: anchor passages paired with current manuscript
   passages (comparative samples), per section.
3. Run with the Fable model. Produce section-by-section rewrite proposals as a
   reviewable diff; autonomous manuscript changes go through branch + PR for
   author arbitration (prose-workpackage rule).
4. Iterate on the author's accept/reject per section.

## Test
- Prose suite green before and after (`tests/test_manuscript_prose.py`);
  ratchet ceilings may tighten, never rise.

## Verification
- [ ] Author reads the diff (latexdiff or PDF) and arbitrates per section
- [ ] AI-tells auditor: no high-confidence hits on the aligned text
- [ ] No content drift: citation keys, numbers, and figure/table references
      byte-identical before/after (grep-verified)

## Invariants
- No factual, numerical, or citation changes — style only.
- No-oversell norms (periodization framing) untouched.
- Œconomia house style (docs/oeconomia-style.md) respected.

## Exit criteria
- [ ] Author signs off the aligned manuscript
- [ ] Full prose + adherence suites green
